## TL;DR

Hey, I'm swyx! I help build great developer experiences, from demos to docs to dev tools to dev communities. I am currently working on the Smol AI Company working in San Francisco and Singapore.

I am also a frequent writer and speaker best known for [the Rise of the AI Engineer](https://www.latent.space/p/ai-engineer) on [Latent Space](https://www.latent.space/), the [Self Provisioning Runtime](https://www.swyx.io/self-provisioning-runtime) and [Third Age of JS](https://www.swyx.io/js-third-age), and finally on the nontechnical side, the [Learn in Public](https://swyx.io/LIP) movement and [The Coding Career Handbook](https://learninpublic.org).

P.S. "swyx" is the initials of my English and Chinese names and you can use it interchangeably with "Shawn". It is pronounced "swicks".

You can find me on [Twitter](https://twitter.com/intent/user?screen_name=swyx), [Github](https://github.com/swyxio) and [YouTube](https://youtube.com/swyxTV?sub_confirmation=1)!

## About

I am a [developer](https://github.com/swyxio)/PM/[angel investor](https://github.com/swyxio/devtools-angels/), primarily active in the AI and devtools community as a blogger and speaker. I am a [GitHub Star](https://stars.github.com/), [Stripe Community Expert](https://twitter.com/swyx/status/1392016498944741376), helped run [the React subreddit for over 200,000 developers](https://www.swyx.io/moderating-rreactjs/) and grew [Svelte Society from 0 to over 15,000 developers](https://twitter.com/swyx/status/1411071913548414976) ([writeup](https://www.swyx.io/starting-dev-community-meetup)).

